Students will obtain knowledge about changes with age in oral cavity and in the development of dental diseases; learn behavioural aspects with elderly and diseased patients while visiting homes for elderly and department of intensive treatment in the hospital diagnosing at the same time oral health problems, giving advice for prevention and performing oral hygiene procedures for the disabled patients. They know special oral hygiene aspects in elderly, are able to design treatment plan according to their general health status.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the study is to learn the changes in the oral cavity, special aspects of dental treatment and prevention of dental diseases in elderly.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students who have passed the course must know how to diagnose and treat diseases of dental hard tissues, periodontal and oral mucosa in elderly.
